The Kaduna State Internal Revenue Service (KADIRS) has sealed off three branches each of the First City Monument Bank (FCMB) and Keystone Bank in Kaduna. Our correspondent gathered that the branches located in Sabon Tasha, Ali Akilu, Bank Road and Yakubu Gowon Way were sealed by the revenue agency over tax liabilities and PAYE. Our correspondent further gathered from credible sources that FCMB is owning over N72milion in tax liabilities while Keystone is owning over N220 million The branches were also sealed over PAYE, non-remittance of PAYE and with holding tax. FG to select teaching hospital for Dutse varsity Kaduna revenue agency seals Access Bank branches over N175m tax Kaduna revenue agency seals-off Access bank branches over N175m tax